.Dd April 19, 2026
.Dt MPORT.QUERY 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm mport.query
.Nd query installed packages using simple predicates
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl c Ar chroot-path
.Op Fl o
.Op Fl q
.Ar query ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
searches the local package database using one or more query predicates joined
with a logical AND.
Supported predicate fields are
.Dq name ,
.Dq origin ,
and
.Dq version .
.Pp
Supported operators are
.Ql = ,
.Ql < ,
.Ql <= ,
.Ql > ,
and
.Ql >= .
The
.Dq name
field uses glob matching.
.Bl -tag -width ".Fl c Ar chroot-path"
.It Fl c Ar chroot-path
Run inside the specified chroot.
.It Fl o
Include package origins in the output.
.It Fl q
Use quiet output.
When combined with
.Fl o ,
print only origins.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
Find installed packages whose names match a glob:
.Dl $ mport.query 'name=python*'
.Pp
Find packages in an origin:
.Dl $ mport.query -o 'origin=lang/python'
.Pp
Find packages newer than a version:
.Dl $ mport.query 'version>=3.11'
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr mport 1 ,
.Xr mport.list 1
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
utility appeared in
.Mx 0.3 .
